### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### BookingSystem API - Test Requests
### Use VS Code REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)
### OR copy the curl equivalents below
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@base = http://localhost:5000

### ── STEP 0: Health Check ─────────────────────────────────────
GET {{base}}/health

### ── STEP 1: List Venues (seeded) ────────────────────────────
GET {{base}}/api/venues

### ── STEP 2: List Customers (seeded) ─────────────────────────
GET {{base}}/api/venues/customers

### ── STEP 3: Check Available Slots ───────────────────────────
# Replace date with any future date
GET {{base}}/api/bookings/slots?venueId=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011&date=2025-12-25

### ── STEP 4: Create a Booking ────────────────────────────────
# This automatically creates a pending Order too
POST {{base}}/api/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "venueId":    "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011",
  "slotDate":   "2025-12-25T11:00:00Z",
  "guestCount": 50
}

### ── STEP 5: Get the Booking ─────────────────────────────────
# Replace {bookingId} with the ID returned in Step 4
GET {{base}}/api/bookings/{{bookingId}}

### ── STEP 6: Pay the Order ────────────────────────────────────
# Replace {orderId} with the order ID from Step 4 response
# Use "fail_card" as cardToken to test payment failure
POST {{base}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}/pay
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cardToken": "valid_token_123"
}

### ── STEP 7: Confirm is auto after payment ────────────────────
GET {{base}}/api/bookings/{{bookingId}}

### ── STEP 8: Get Customer's Bookings ─────────────────────────
GET {{base}}/api/bookings/customer/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001

### ── STEP 9: Cancel a Booking ────────────────────────────────
POST {{base}}/api/bookings/{{bookingId}}/cancel
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "Customer requested cancellation"
}

### ── STEP 10: Test Payment Failure ───────────────────────────
# First create another booking
POST {{base}}/api/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002",
  "venueId":    "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000012",
  "slotDate":   "2025-12-26T14:00:00Z",
  "guestCount": 20
}

### Then pay with a failing token
POST {{base}}/api/orders/{{orderId2}}/pay
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cardToken": "fail_card_test"
}

### ── STEP 11: See all published Domain Events ─────────────────
GET {{base}}/api/events

### ── STEP 12: Run full demo in ONE call ──────────────────────
# Creates booking → order → pays → confirms automatically
POST {{base}}/api/demo/full-flow


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### EQUIVALENT CURL COMMANDS
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Health check
# curl http://localhost:5000/health

# List venues
# curl http://localhost:5000/api/venues

# Create booking
# curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/bookings \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -d '{"customerId":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001","venueId":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011","slotDate":"2025-12-25T11:00:00Z","guestCount":50}'

# Full demo
# curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/demo/full-flow
